<p class="fd-paragraph">
  Machina unifies SMS, telephony, and video into a single communication layer — with AI agents that can initiate, route, and resolve patient interactions autonomously. Every channel is logged, contextualized, and actionable without manual intervention.
</p>

<h2 class="fd-section-heading">What it does</h2>
<ul class="fd-list">
  <li class="fd-list-item">Unified inbox across SMS, voice, and video — no channel switching</li>
  <li class="fd-list-item">AI agents initiate outreach, respond to inbound, and escalate intelligently</li>
  <li class="fd-list-item">Every interaction is automatically logged and linked to the patient record</li>
  <li class="fd-list-item">Real-time routing based on acuity, availability, and patient preference</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="fd-section-heading">Why it matters</h2>
<p class="fd-paragraph">
  Care teams spend significant time managing communication across fragmented tools. Omni Channel eliminates that overhead — agents handle the volume, humans handle the judgment.
</p>
